summary: Headcanon that crowley is very uncomfortable with steak served bloody while aziraphale is not. Thoughts?
question: Headcanon that crowley is very uncomfortable with steak served bloody while aziraphale is not. Thoughts?

summary: So @bringthekaos and I live together and we have this chalk board by the front door to leave each other notes- hey we need eggs,...

Things like that. Well this has taken over the chalk board for the last month or two and it serves as my daily reminder to have a mini panic attack every time I get to change the number. summary: aj ur trope is the oracle from an adventure movie that only speaks in riddles (or in this case Olde Englishe) but instead of...
question: aj ur trope is the oracle from an adventure movie that only speaks in riddles (or in this case Olde Englishe) but instead of greek mythology its jewish and instead of being wizened and gross ur moominmamma's humansona
answer:
To get ludicrously technical, what I’m using on @ask-agnes-nutter is an imitation of the parody-version of Early Modern English that Pratchett and Gaiman used.  However, my graduate-school years were spent working with and transcribing Middle English dialects from about 1100 - 1500, so I think my Agnes is as strongly-influenced by Middle English as Early Modern English.  I’ve seen so many wacky regional spelling variants from both periods that gravitating to a baseline average is easy.

TL;DR I’m a linguistics nerd, and your assessment pleases my puzzle-loving Jewish heart very much.  I don’t know as much about Moomins as I should!

(In my mind’s eye, you’re the artsy, enigmatic photographer trope.  Nobody knows why you take so many photos, or what you do with them.)
